  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "I'm using v2.9.1.\r\n\r\nIf there is a previous request made from a non empty account value to a contract running on Hardhat and the next request is made with an empty account value Hardhat keeps returning results as if the request was made with the previous account.\r\nThe account value is internally cached and doesn't change if the new account value is empty.\r\n\r\nThis only happens when the request is from an empty account.\r\n\r\nRequest 1 with Account1 -> Hardhat -> data of Account1 is returned.\r\nRequest 2 with empty account value -> Hardhat -> data of Account1 is returned again.\r\nRequest 3 with Account2 -> Hardhat -> data of Account2 is returned.",
